[{"id":"VR871166","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Bismuth-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"212\"><math alttext=\"212\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>212</mn></math></span></span> has a half-life of about <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60\"><math alttext=\"60\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>60</mn></math></span></span> minutes. It decays and becomes thallium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span> in 36% of the cases and polonium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span> in 64% of the cases. Thallium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span> has a half-life of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> minutes and decays to become the stable isotope lead-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span>. Polonium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span> has a half-life of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"299\"><math alttext=\"299\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>299</mn></math></span></span> nanoseconds and also decays to lead-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span>. Consider a sample of bismuth atoms. After <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60\"><math alttext=\"60\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>60</mn></math></span></span> minutes, which of the following claims about the sample is correct?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871166_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The total mass is about half of the original mass.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The number of lead-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span> atoms is close to half of the original number of bismuth-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"212\"><math alttext=\"212\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>212</mn></math></span></span> atoms.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The sample is almost entirely comprised of lead-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The atoms in the sample are 50% bismuth-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"212\"><math alttext=\"212\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>212</mn></math></span></span>, 18% thallium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span>, and 32% polonium-<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"208\"><math alttext=\"208\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>208</mn></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":1}]